s/pilot/agent.yaml` (added in commit `9b3ef5d`) has no `belayer_tools` field at all. The `agents.md` for this template shows it should be able to spawn agents (`belayer session add-agent`). Since the daemon looks up `templates/&lt;name&gt;/agent.yaml` using the agent's `Name` field, if someone spawns an agent named `\"pilot\"` using these examples, it will get only baseline tools (send_message, report_status, create_artifact) — not `belayer_spawn_agent`. The template is silently broken for its intended use case. This is distinct from the `templates/supervisor/` templates which are correctly configured.\n\n### 6. PM auto-spawn uses Profile: \"default\" with no fallback documentation\n\nIn `bridge_events.go` `handleBridgeCompletionRequested`, the auto-spawned PM agent uses `Profile: \"default\"`. There is no validation that a \"default\" profile exists in the Hermes installation. If Hermes doesn't have a \"default\" profile, the PM spawn will fail and the supervisor gets a retry message — the run becomes stuck in a completion-requested state. Previously the code had the same issue (commit `6697e66`), so this is not a regression, just a pre-existing risk that the PR didn't address.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of severity:**\n- **High (functional)**: SKILL.md files not renamed — specialists receive instructions to message \"planner\" which routes nowhere\n- **Medium (functional)**: examples/templates/pilot missing belayer_tools — silently broken for any run using that template\n- **Low (latent)**: inline YAML list format silently ignored\n- **Cosmetic**: test comments/names in bridge_events_test.go and store_test.go still say \"planner\"</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>72738</total_tokens><tool_uses>101</tool_uses><duration_ms>364268</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>",
